title: At 17, iPhone debuts at India’s largest factory
description: Apple's largest iPhone production facility in India, operated by Foxconn, is now fully operational, manufacturing the iPhone 17. The factory, employing 25,000 workers with plans to reach 100,000, signifies India's growing importance as an Apple production hub.

title: Apple’s iPhones Are Now Made in India—Is Tim Cook’s Tariff Headache Over?
description: Apple’s iPhone 17 debuts slimmer and India-made, reflecting its push to shift production from China and sidestep Trump’s tariffs.
